track_notes:
From I-25 exit at Los Lunas.  Turn west and drive up the hill on NM-6 until you reach Tower Road.  Take Tower Road south.  It will make a left turn at the tower.  Continue east until you reach the gate.  Park.

Follow the main trail east.  The trail will turn left for a distance, then back right again.  As you approach a deep arroyo the trail will again go to the left along the arroyo, then turn right for the final ascent to the summit.

From I-25, exit at Los Lunas.  Go west up Main St (NM-6) to Huning Ranch Loop.  Turn left on the loop.  Follow the loop to Lonestar St, turn right.  Immediately turn left, then right, then left again until you reach the dead-end where the dirt trail begins.

Follow the main trail to the summit.  At times the trail will become deep sand and will be steep, other places are quite rocky.  There will be a covered picnic table about half-way to the summit.
